Class ISNI

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<ISNI>, StandardNumber
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ORCID

    public class ISNI
extends AbstractStandardNumber
implements Comparable<ISNI>, StandardNumber
    ISO 27729 International Standard Name Identifier (ISNI) The International Standard Name Identifier (ISNI) is a method for uniquely identifying the public identities of contributors to media content such as books, TV programmes, and newspaper articles. Such an identifier consists of 16 numerical digits divided into four blocks. Checksum is in accordance to ISO/IEC 7064:2003, MOD 11-2
